    reasoning: "The only prompt change was a rewording of line 19: the old text spelled out the mechanism (\"Add a path dependency on each in your Cargo.toml ... use their public API, and do not reimplement their logic or depend on any hand-written crate\") while the new text states the same three requirements more tightly (\"Use each generated sibling crate's public API — do not reimplement its types or logic here, and do not depend on any hand-written crate\"). No named symbol, field, signature, struct, or behavior changed. The existing source already satisfies the new wording: incremental/Cargo.toml carries path deps on schemas_line_range and schemas_attribution (which, in a Cargo workspace, is how a sibling crate's public API is consumed), lib.rs uses their public types rather than reimplementing them, and no hand-written crate is depended upon. Tests pass 11/11. Editing source would be no-op churn against the \"touch nothing outside incremental/\" and minimal-edit constraints."
  - promptLines:
